sentences: The original YouTube channel used from January to April 2016 was named GiIvaSunner, named after the former soundtrack ripping YouTube channel GilvaSunner, but spelled with a capital "i" used in place of a lowercase "L" (with the effect of making the channels confusingly similar).
Following the termination of their original YouTube channel in April 2016, the name was changed to SiIvaGunner for the new channel (retaining the capital "i").
As of May 2021, the channel's more than 16,000 videos have accumulated over 800 million views, and at least 39 of its videos have surpassed 1 million views.
In late 2019, art gallery Gallery Aferro featured an exhibit titled "Elevator Music 6: SiIvaGunner", curated by Juno Zago.
